locList.addLoc("pc_gas_giant_hot","Ultra Giant","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_gas_giant_hot_desc","A large gaseous planet with an atmosphere primarily composed of hydrogen and helium. The planet is in close proximity to the parent star and so has a very high surface temperature and a short orbital period. The atmosphere is extreme and exotic due to the short period and long days, with intense winds and super-rotating equatorial jet streams.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geocrystalline","Cambrian World","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geocrystalline_desc","After the core of a Primordial planet is sufficiently cool, volcanic activity lessens and conditions for life improve. Oxygen and Nitrogen are present in some abundance in the atmosphere, giving rise to increasingly complex organisms such as primitive vegetation like algae, and animal akin to sponges and jellyfish. As the planet continues to cool, it can finally transition into the final stage of its evolution.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geocrystalline_habitability","Cambrian Habitability","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geocrystalline_tile","Rocky Terrain","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geocrystalline_tile_desc","Dry and rocky terrain with sparse vegetation.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geometallic","Primordial World","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geometallic_desc","As a Molten world cools, the crust and core solidify and the planet can become Primordial if conditions are right. These barren worlds are witness to much geologic activity, steam expelled from volcanic eruptions condenses into water and forms the first shallow seas, in which bacteria may develop and ultimately thrive. As the core of a Primordial planet cools, the volcanic activity lessens and the planet eventually transitions to a more inhabitable class.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geometallic_terraforming","Primordial World (Terraforming)","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geometallic_terraforming_habitability","Primordial Habitability","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geometallic_terraforming_tile","Barren Terrain","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geometallic_terraforming_tile_desc","Rocky and lifeless terrain.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geomorteus","Radiated World","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geomorteus_desc","Small, rocky worlds located within a star system's hot zone. Unsuitable for humanoid life, these planets have highly unstable radiated surfaces. The thin atmospheres are composed primarily of helium and sodium. In the harsh daylight, temperatures can approach 450º Celsius, because there is little atmosphere to retain that heat, it can get as cold as -200º Celsius at night. No life forms have ever been observed on Radiated worlds.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geomorteus_terraforming","Radiated World (Terraforming)","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geomorteus_terraforming_habitability","Radiated Habitability","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geomorteus_terraforming_tile","Radiated Terrain","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geomorteus_terraforming_tile_desc","Rocky and barren terrain, scorched due to close proximity to the parent star.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geoplastic","Molten World","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_geoplastic_desc","These worlds represent the earliest stage in the formation of a habitable planet. The core and crust are completely molten, making the planet susceptible to solar winds and radiation, and subject to extremely high surface temperatures. The atmosphere is very thin and composed of hydrogen and helium. As the planet cools, the core and crust begin to harden and the planet can become Primordial if conditions are right.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_greenhouse_cold","Cold Reducing World","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_greenhouse_cold_desc","A rocky planet with a dense atmosphere. Despite being far from the parent star, the gases in the atmosphere have caused a greenhouse effect, allowing exotic liquids such as methane and ethane to exist on the surface.","en")
locList.addLoc("pc_greenhouse_cold_terraforming","Cold Reducing World (Terraforming)","en")
